Info.Name: Player name 1
Info.Desc: Your avatar in this world. A special character who can take up any Life class.

Info.Name: Daniel
Info.Desc: A Miner and former team member of Duglas and Rocque. Befriends Moley. Keeps finger on the pulse.

Info.Name: Castele Resident
Info.Desc: A lady who's good at cooking. She's always thinking about what to cook for dinner.

Info.Name: Shop Assistant
Info.Desc: A young man fond of honey. However, he's too afraid of bees to get the honey himself.

Info.Name: Shop Assistant
Info.Desc: The poster girl of a fashion boutique. Isn't aware of her own popularity. The younger of the two twins.

Info.Name: Shop Assistant
Info.Desc: A Carpenter under training who admires Woody. A helpful youth who loves desserts.

Info.Name: Shop Assistant
Info.Desc: Daughter of Vulcan the Blacksmith. Her name resembles the sound produced when striking iron. (Prev: Castele Vender Female)

Info.Name: Royal Butler
Info.Desc: Servant of a great scholar. Always worrying about the scholar's health. A worrywart.

Info.Name: Royal Maidservant
Info.Desc: A maid who loves fruits. She enjoys feeding her lady yummy fruits.

Info.Name: Castele Resident
Info.Desc: A well-informed middle-aged man. The hat that's red as an apple is his trademark.

Info.Name: Castele Kid
Info.Desc: An energetic boy who often runs about hunting rare insects.

Info.Name: Bo
Info.Desc: An energetic boy who often runs about hunting rare insects.

Info.Name: Marimo
Info.Desc: A great Carpenter you often hear about in legends, whose current whereabouts is known by little.

Info.Name: Crowned Champion
Info.Desc: The former Castele King who loves nature. He enjoys his current carefree life and is not getting back to town.

Info.Name: Crowned Champion
Info.Desc: The former Castele King who loves nature. He enjoys his current carefree life and is not getting back to town.

Info.Name: Butch
Info.Desc: Pretends to be a scoundrel but is actually a talkative coward who likes to be with people. Always interfering others' business.

Info.Name: Ironsmith
Info.Desc: A skillful Blacksmith wearing a mysterious mask. Nobody knows his true identity.

Info.Name: Forrest
Info.Desc: A seasoned Carpenter living in the forest. An old acquaintance of Heyho. Fell in love with the Goddess of the spring water.

Info.Name: Pagiello
Info.Desc: A Cook for Cocina Rica by day and for the pirates by night. A Cook with two identities.

Info.Name: Pierre
Info.Desc: A nosy middle-aged man who considers himself in charge of the Castele mafia. Goes berserk occasionally.

Info.Name: Mysterious Elder
Info.Desc: A mysterious being at Starlight Garden. His origins are unknown. He speaks in a way as if he knows everything about the world.

Info.Name: Mysterious Elder
Info.Desc: A mysterious being at Starlight Garden. His origins are unknown. He speaks in a way as if he knows everything about the world.

Info.Name: Celestia
Info.Desc: The Goddess who brings Lives to this world. She pities those who don't work.

Info.Name: Prof. Snooze
Info.Desc: An elderly Alchemist who founded the Laboratory. His true power is revealed when asleep.

Info.Name: Isobel
Info.Desc: A nice Paladin with strong wrists. He's actually fond of cute things.

Info.Name: Melusine
Info.Desc: The keeper of the sealed cave on Cactus Cove. Raised as the grandson of Miguel. A skilled sword wielder.

Info.Name: Monika
Info.Desc: A quiet girl who loves nature and cares for her father. She is more knowledgeable about the forest than anyone else.

Info.Name: Monika
Info.Desc: A quiet girl who loves nature and cares for her father. She is more knowledgeable about the forest than anyone else.

Info.Name: Allan
Info.Desc: A Palace Chef acknowledged by the royal family. His signature dish is hamburger steak.

Info.Name: Magmia
Info.Desc: A young Blacksmith gaining recognition at the Artisans' District. Worried about her useless Paladin older brother.

Info.Desc: A young Blacksmith gaining recognition at the Artisans' District. Worried about her useless Paladin older brother.

Info.Name: Colin
Info.Desc: A wandering Magician burdened with the mission of suppressing runaway spirits. Can use Light and sealing magic.

Info.Name: Colin
Info.Desc: A wandering Magician burdened with the mission of suppressing runaway spirits. Can use Light and sealing magic.

Info.Name: Ignatius
Info.Desc: A rookie Paladin who's pessimistic towards everything. He was supposed to carry on his father's job as a Blacksmith, but he keeps that a secret.

Info.Name: Porthos
Info.Desc: A Paladin with notable stamina. He likes eating and talking about food. Calls himself the Wall of Castele.

Info.Name: Laura (Young)
Info.Desc: The only daughter of Erik and Ophelia. As righteous as her father and as gentle as her mother.

Info.Name: Laura (Young)
Info.Desc: The only daughter of Erik and Ophelia. As righteous as her father and as gentle as her mother.

Info.Name: Roslyn
Info.Desc: A rookie Paladin filled with hope and dreams. Her favorite saying is, "Talent is limited, but hard work is not."

Info.Name: Ophelia
Info.Desc: The naive Queen consort of Castele. She takes care of her beloved husband and their daughter.

Info.Desc: A disappointing Hunter who is all talk. Supposedly, he became a Hunter to gain popularity among girls.

Info.Name: Olivia
Info.Desc: A young girl who is the head of both pirates and aristocrats of Port Puerto. Usually tough and loves to win, but she also has her sensitive side.

Info.Name: Yuelia
Info.Desc: A girl you encountered at Origin Island on Namona. She has a mysterious air about her.

Info.Desc: The poster girl of Anglers' Association and currently the No. 1 Angler. She's like an elder sister to Guppy.

Info.Name: Guppy
Info.Desc: Grandson to the Master of Anglers' Association. Crude and careless, but good at fishing. He's too young to travel far.

Info.Name: Gustaf
Info.Desc: A Mercenary on a mission at Mt Snowpeak whose loyalty towards employers is widely acknowledged.

Info.Name: Jude
Info.Desc: A cowardly and somehow pessimistic Mercenary who claims that running away is also an option.

Info.Name: Leilah
Info.Desc: A girl who lives in the Elderwood hinterlands among spirits. She has replaced her older brother as a Guardian of the Forest to watch over Elderwood.

Info.Name: Leilah
Info.Desc: A girl from Elderwood who calls herself a Guardian of the Forest. It's the first time she has left the forest, which makes her a bit nervous.

Info.Name: Orlando
Info.Desc: A young man devoted to logging. A man of few words, and especially poor at talking to females, which troubles himself a lot.

Info.Name: Snowman
Info.Desc: A young man devoted to logging. A man of few words, and especially poor at talking to females, which troubles himself a lot.

Info.Name: Chic
Info.Desc: A prominent designer of the Hictick brand. Looks after Madam Purl's house when she is away.

Info.Name: Glenn
Info.Desc: A lone-wolf Mercenary known as the Dragonslayer. They say he can cut the body of dragons apart, and that he even outpowers the divine.

Info.Name: Glenn
Info.Desc: A tough Mercenary who suddenly appeared in Namona. Skeptical about God's Envoy but teamed up to investigate abnormities.

Info.Name: Decker
Info.Desc: A straightforward Carpenter who treats all work seriously. Enjoys tea breaks right after work.

Info.Name: Cherry
Info.Desc: Woody's little sister. Though still young, she has the potential to become a great Carpenter. The owner of Beavy and Beavo.

Info.Name: Petri
Info.Desc: A skittish young Alchemist who seems to be an apprentice of Flamel. However, it's yet to be confirmed since the latter doesn't remember it.

Info.Name: Nox
Info.Desc: A shy Magician with a competitive personality. He's still a child and admires his elder brother, who is away.

Info.Desc: An Alchemist and an expert in making accessories. She calls herself an ally of youths in love.

Info.Desc: A dream-pursuing Miner, who dreams of traveling to distant places in the future.

Info.Name: Mustang
Info.Desc: The Captain of the Paladins that is trusted by his subordinates and a Master Paladin. A stickler about beards.

Info.Name: Cervantes
Info.Desc: An elderly Mercenary who has had several narrow escapes from death and considers himself as capable as in his youth.

Info.Name: Fern
Info.Desc: The cold and strict Master Hunter who's now an undercover agent serving under Castele's royalty.

Info.Name: Jinx
Info.Desc: A cat, but the Master Magician as well. She may not look like it, but she's very skillful.

Info.Name: Duglas
Info.Desc: The confused Master Miner. Extremely enthusiastic, and now passing his enthusiasm to his apprentices.

Info.Name: Heyho
Info.Desc: The earnest and taciturn Master Woodcutter. Loved by trees, and loves trees so deeply that he is unable to cut them down.

Info.Name: Fisherman Sage
Info.Desc: The competent Master Angler. They say he once traveled the world. Now lives in the solitude of the mountains.

Info.Name: Alfredo
Info.Desc: The Master Cook who's always starving, whose motto is to eat while cooking.

Info.Name: Vulcan
Info.Desc: The Master Blacksmith who's strict with both himself and others. A most devoted craftsman who detests dabblers.

Info.Name: Woody
Info.Desc: The frank and laid-back Master Carpenter who doesn't feel like working or having any apprentices.

Info.Name: Madam Purl
Info.Desc: The broad-minded and gentle Master Tailor who enjoys seeing grandchildren growing up.

Info.Name: Flamel
Info.Desc: The trouble-making Master Alchemist who loves bombs. Interested only in Alchemy that concerns explosion.

Info.Name: Plushling Blackmarket Merchant
Info.Desc: A mysterious Plushling often appearing out of nowhere who sells rare items that are hard to obtain.

Info.Name: Sir Co-op
Info.Desc: A staff member and gatekeeper of the Co-op mode portal. Talk to him if you want to play with friends.

Info.Name: Gatekeeper
Info.Desc: She keeps her appearance perfect to greet visitors at all times. Even the angle of the entrance was designed after careful consideration.

Info.Name: God's Messenger
Info.Desc: Sorts and reports the latest news concerning divines. Gets fatigued when in areas with poor signal reception.

Info.Name: God's Shop Assistant
Info.Desc: She sells impressive items containing Divine Power. A bit intimidated by her new identity as a poster girl.

Info.Name: God's Gatekeeper
Info.Desc: Struggles to stay awake while keeping the magic circle for sending users to the mortal realm. Usually listless, but becomes excited when the magic circle is activated.

Info.Name: Quest Manager
Info.Desc: Introduces quests from guilds all over the world. Gets to the sites in-person first, but always ends up getting beaten up.

Info.Name: Beauty Salon Staff
Info.Desc: Can change the appearance of God's Envoy. To train aesthetic tastes, will collect all kinds of beautiful items. Troubled by not being able to paint skillfully.

Info.Name: Sir Guild
Info.Desc: Always sees adventurers off cheerfully when they go on an adventure. Learning swordsmanship in order to go with them one day.

Info.Name: Sir Guild
Info.Desc: Always sees adventurers off cheerfully when they go on an adventure. Learning swordsmanship in order to go with them one day.

Info.Name: Stardust Shop Assistant
Info.Desc: Trades weapons and armor summoned for Pts., which can then be used to purchase special items here.

Info.Name: Buto
Info.Desc:
God of Strength
Bold and Enthusiastic

Info.Name: Jaken
Info.Desc:
God of Wisdom
Calm and Rational

Info.Name: Bunny
Info.Desc: A rabbit with a fierce look but likes to be with people. It sometimes pleads for food.

Info.Name: Bouncy Bunny
Info.Desc: Has good hearing. Will be scared even by the flapping of insect wings. A bit annoying when it jumps around.

Info.Name: Bunny Killer
Info.Desc: A wolf that thrives in the environments of Levitania. You cannot tell by looking at it, but it hates being poked by grass.

Info.Name: Pandemonium
Info.Desc: It looks like a panda, but is actually something more violent. However, it can't help but play with tires.

Info.Name: Killer Bear
Info.Desc: A bear known for its fierceness. Whenever it gets a chance, it starts boasting about how it got the scar on its eye.

Info.Name: Great Horn
Info.Desc: A goat proud of its long hair and huge horns. The males fight each other during mating seasons.

Info.Name: Banana King
Info.Desc: A gorilla that stays energetic all day long. The banana growing from its head is always fresh and sweet.

Info.Name: Behemoth
Info.Desc: A monster that makes even the strongest Miners to cower in fear. It actually feeds on mushrooms.

Info.Name: Gigante
Info.Desc: A showy monster with flames for a mane. It's good at beat-boxing.

Info.Name: Green Gator
Info.Desc: An athletic croc fond of jogging. It likes to be greeted enthusiastically.

Info.Name: Croc
Info.Desc: A croc that secretly protects the one it loves. When it's heartbroken, the flower on its head withers.

Info.Name: Trihorn
Info.Desc: A dinosaur with huge horns and hard scales. Its buttocks are relatively weak to attacks.

Info.Name: Silverfang
Info.Desc: A dinosaur said to be capable of generating blizzards. It likes the sound of stepping on snow.

Info.Name: Ferociousaurus
Info.Desc: A dinosaur too violent to deal with. It likes to eat meat together with bananas.

Info.Name: Shadowsaurus
Info.Desc: A Ferociousaurus affected by Shadow Power. Even harder to deal with.

Info.Name: Great Serpent
Info.Desc: A great serpent that grew up by the sea. It mainly feeds on sea cucumbers and sea snails.

Info.Name: King Cobra
Info.Desc: A great serpent that grew up in the ruins. It has the habit of stealing the crowns of mummies.

Info.Name: Crocturtle
Info.Desc: A turtle notable in both attack and defense. It can crush sea snails and oysters with its jaw.

Info.Name: Chop-Chop Piranha
Info.Desc: Hatchet chop chop. Hi guys. To think that hatchet on its nose is actually one of the three delicacies.

Info.Name: Octoshell
Info.Desc: An octopus carrying a self-made pot. It can sleep in the pot.

Info.Name: Black Octoshell
Info.Desc: An octopus that dyed itself black by mistake. Its heart is not black, though. It easily feels lonely.

Info.Name: Octoshell Knight
Info.Desc: An octopus that uses a shell to protect its soft body. It used to clamp down on its feet a lot in its youth.

Info.Name: Saw Shark
Info.Desc: No matter how big the prey is, this big eater cuts it into pieces and eat. It evolved from a saw dropped by a Carpenter into the sea.

Info.Name: Shadow Shark
Info.Desc: A Bitey Shark affected by Shadow Power. It no longer feels like playing pranks.

Info.Name: Spiked Jellyfish
Info.Desc: A deep-sea jellyfish whose thorns are slightly toxic. It's quite delicious and chewy when made into sashimi.

Info.Name: Electro Jellyfish
Info.Desc: A beautiful jellyfish with patterns that resemble the starry sky. Try looking at the moon through its bell.

Info.Name: Sharp Weedling
Info.Desc: A grass that has turned from the mowed to the mower. Really wants to give humans a taste of being mowed.

Info.Name: Terror Weedling
Info.Desc: Short-tempered grass that disapproves of the food chain. It wants to be superior to herbivores.

Info.Name: Cactus
Info.Desc: A mean cactus that is popular among children. Descendent of the huge cactus on the island.

Info.Name: Flowering Cactus
Info.Desc: A maiden cactus that likes fashion and flower petal fortune-telling. Trying hard to bloom flowers.

Info.Name: Burrly Bramble
Info.Desc: A fallen tree brought to life by the breath of forest. The mushroom on its head has its own mind.

Info.Name: Punching Palm
Info.Desc: A living tree with coconuts as its fists. It came to life when dancing in the wind.

Info.Name: Brutal Blossom
Info.Desc: A carnivorous plant that has grown too big. It wants to go looking for preys instead of waiting.

Info.Name: Violent Violet
Info.Desc: A greedy and attractive predator. The luring lips bring animals to it.

Info.Name: Batmon
Info.Desc: A devil born from the resentment lingering in the ruins. Those huge ears can always catch the sound of Dosh.

Info.Name: Chiromon
Info.Desc: A devil born from the regret of dead adventurers. Those huge eyes are always looking for treasure.

Info.Name: Darkmon
Info.Desc: A Batmon affected by Shadow Power. Its resentment has been boosted significantly.

Info.Name: Angry Zombie
Info.Desc: A pirate who died fighting for the position of captain. It wants to go back to the pirate ship.

Info.Name: Jelling
Info.Desc: A sea cow that likes moss on the seafloor. It sometimes eats shellfish as well.

Info.Name: Lava Jelling
Info.Desc: A sea cow that feeds on lava of Mt Snowpeak. It's hot enough to be used for heating.

Info.Name: Toxic Jelling
Info.Desc: A sea cow that feeds on toxic mushrooms of the Subterranean Lake. It tastes like grapes, but is deadly poisonous.

Info.Name: Desert Jelling
Info.Desc: A sea cow that likes sand in the desert. It uses Armordillo to hold sand.

Info.Name: Metal Jelling
Info.Desc: A sea cow that mainly feeds on rust. It can renew rusted frying pans.

Info.Name: Jellking
Info.Desc: A giant sea cow merged from 8 sea cows. However, it only grants XP slightly more than that of 5 sea cows.

Info.Name: Ironstone Golem
Info.Desc: A golem born from iron sand. It feels inferior because it's a bit rusted.

Info.Name: Lava Golem
Info.Desc: A golem born from lava. It breathes fire to express its emotions.

Info.Name: Pickaxed Golem
Info.Desc: A rock salt golem with a pickaxe stabbed in its body which hurts a bit, but it likes it.

Info.Name: Gilded Golem
Info.Desc: A golem born from sand containing gold. A rich guy who likes to be talked about.

Info.Name: Mimic
Info.Desc: A monster waiting for adventurers deep in the ruins. Anyone who sees it will be pulled into another world.

Info.Name: Mothoon

Info.Name: Theia
Info.Desc: A subordinate of the Chaos Dragon. To make a certain wish come true, it robbed Yuelia's Goddess Power and is attempting to revive the Chaos Dragon.

Info.Name: Zeo
Info.Desc: A Shadow Dragonslayer whose purpose of life is to spread despair. He looks the same as Glenn, but his origin is unknown.

Info.Name: Snow
Info.Desc: The super-popular Idol whose smile is as shiny as snowflakes. She's going to deliver excitement in her imp swimsuit.

Info.Name: Brown Horse
Info.Desc:
A brown horse quite common on the prairie.
It's calm and like to be near humans.

Info.Name: Black horse
Info.Desc:
A black horse quite common on the prairie.
It's wild and arrogant and challenging to approach.

Info.Name: Pegasus
Info.Desc:
A legendary horse of heaven which gallops freely in the sky.
Legend states that it was enchanted
to send a princess to a ball long ago.

Info.Name: Unicorn
Info.Desc:
An illusory unicorn living in the depth of the forest.
According to legend, it only appears to those with pure hearts.

Info.Name: Star Steed
Info.Desc:
A rare horse that emits a blue light.
It looks like a comet when running through fields.

Info.Name: Pounding Alpaca
Info.Desc:
Never passes an opportunity to fall in love.
An alpaca lady that is always jubilant.

Info.Name: Napdragon Bike
Info.Desc:
A motorbike inspired by the Napdragon.
If you ride it haphazardly, you'll be tossed to the ground as if you'd awakened the dragon.

Info.Name: Black Dragon Bike
Info.Desc:
Featuring an exquisitely-designed exterior,
it resembles the rebirth of the Black Dragon.
To prioritize its speed, every piece of its parts is made of light materials.
